clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of hypertension angina and arrhythmia

contraindications.disease: LD sub 50 sub 597 0 mg kg Orally in rats
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Alprenolol is a non selective beta blocker used in the treatment of hypertension edema ventricular tachycardias and atrial fibrillation Alprenolol impairs AV node conduction and decreases sinus rate and may also increase plasma triglycerides and decrease HDL cholesterol levels Alprenolol is nonpolar and hydrophobic with low to moderate lipid solubility Alprenolol has little to no intrinsic sympathomimetic activity and unlike some other beta adrenergic blocking agents alprenolol has little direct myocardial depressant activity and does not have an anesthetic like membrane stabilizing action
